We demand that the transformed coordinates  also satisfy the commutator 
(). 
The Poincare quantum group does not determined only by the covariance 
of the commutator. Furthermore we demand that differentiation with respect to  
is not deformed;
dX^ dX^ =-dX^ dX^ . 
In order for the condition () to be compatible with the Poincare quantum group,
() have to be commutative with all of the elements of the quantum group. By 
using the conditions, the Poincare quantum group is determined uniquely;
