Summary and remarks 
In this paper, we have investigated free particle's motion in the -Minkowski 
spacetime in which the Poincare group becomes the quantum group. The particle's action 
is not -deformed, since the invariant metric of the -Minkowski spacetime does 
not have  -dependence in our formalism. When we 
define particle's velocity, there exists uncertainty of the velocity because the 
spacetime coordinates are non-commutative operators with the commutator (). 
The point is different from the 
discussions in momentum spaces. We saw that the 
particle's velocity can depend on , even if the action is -independent. 
In ordinary relativistic classical theories, massless particles propagate only with 
the velocity  which is defined by . However in the -Minkowski 
spacetime, the massless particle's velocity have the uncertainty   
. V^2_min  -3c^2  L 
which does not depend on the energy of the particle but on the propagation length  of 
the particle. When  is small, so is the spacetime uncertainty 
(). However for a small , the velocity's uncertainty is large.  
The constant  can be interpreted as the expectation value of the photon's velocity.

In order to compatible with the observed value of , we have the bound 
. 
The typical length of light paths in experiments of velocity of light is of order 
-1m. 
So  is m which is weaker restriction than the one which is derived by 
using the formula ().
In a non-relativistic limit , the uncertainty () of the 
velocity can be negligible. The result is compatible with the fact that the only Lorentz 
boost part of the Poincare algebra is -deformed.




